{
  "texts": [
    "The comparison includes the true proto-halo segmentation, alongside predictions from our CNN-based model (copra), ViT-based model (vipr), and, for reference, the perturbation-theory-based model pinocchio [36,37].",
    "pinocchio (v. 4.1.2) was run with the same initial conditions as our simulations, employing second-order LPT for group finding and third-order LPT for displacements, the latter being irrelevant for the present analysis.",
    "Each panel highlights the voxel-wise classification into the different mass bins of dataset 3, as well as the non-halo (background) class.",
    "This example offers a first impression of the segmentation capabilities of each method, and allows for a visual inspection of similarities and discrepancies in predicting proto-halo morphology and spatial extent.Although all methods produce qualitatively similar outputs at first glance, a closer inspection reveals clear differences in fidelity with respect to the ground truth.",
    "Among the models, copra and vipr yield the most accurate and spatially coherent predictions, closely matching the true proto-halo regions."
  ]
}